lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5121  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"Double-labeling of sensory neurons with antibodies against CRMP-2 and the synaptic vesicle marker synaptophysin (Ichikawa et al., 1991) revealed extensive colocalization of CRMP-2 in synaptophysin-positive puncta (Fig. 6B), wherein 85±12% (n=468) of synapses were labeled with both proteins (Fig. 6D). To test whether endogenous CRMP-2 was targeted to functionally active synapses and/or release sites, neurons were loaded with the membrane-bound dye FM4-64 by stimulation with 90 mM KCl. Neurons loaded with FM dye were then fixed and labeled with an antibody against CRMP-2 (Fig. 6Ci). Of the functionally active FM-dye-loaded release sites, 78±17% (n=347) were positive for CRMP-2, thus indicating that CRMP-2 is targeted to functional synapses (Fig. 6Ciii,D).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"C57BL/6 mice (3-6 months old) and Sprague-Dawley rats (100-150 g) were purchased from Harlan Laboratories (Indianapolis, IN).\"\n\nantibody:\npolyclonal CRMP-2 (Cell Signaling Technology, MA)\nmonoclonal CRMP-2 (Abcam, Cambridge, MA)\n\nValidated siRNAs against the rat or mouse CRMP-2 [5'-ACTCCTTCCTCGTGTACAT-3'] sequence (Nishimura et al., 2003) were from Invitrogen.\n\nBLAST confirmed ACTCCTTCCTCGTGTACAT matched GenBank accession NM_001378767 --> Entrez Gene 12934 (Dpysl2)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5121" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

